<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[tokumaru]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-10-03T05:53:01-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-10-03T05:53:01-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8175&amp;p=84623#p84623</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8175&amp;p=84623#p84623"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Error graphics at the top of the screen]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8175&amp;p=84623#p84623"><![CDATA[
If you set the vertical scroll to values between 240 and 255 you force the NES to render attribute table data as if it was name table data. If you do like tepples said instead and set the scroll to 232, the PPU will render 8 scanlines and automatically wrap from 239 to 0. That's normal PPU behavior.<br /><br />As long as you write that diagonal pattern to the last 2 rows of the name table and use vertical mirroring, a scroll value of 232 should result in the effect you're going for.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Mon Oct 03, 2011 5:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
